# DedgeAuth Build and Deploy

## App Inventory

| App | Source Path | DotNetDll | ApiPort | IIS Path |
|-----|------------|-----------|---------|----------|
| **DedgeAuth** (server) | `C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth` | `DedgeAuth.Api.dll` | 8100 | `/DedgeAuth` |
| **DocView** | `C:\opt\src\DocView` | `DocView.dll` | 8282 | `/DocView` |
| **GenericLogHandler** | `C:\opt\src\GenericLogHandler` | `GenericLogHandler.WebApi.dll` | 8110 | `/GenericLogHandler` |
| **ServerMonitorDashboard** | `C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor` | `ServerMonitorDashboard.dll` | 8998 | `/ServerMonitorDashboard` |
| **AutoDocJson** | `C:\opt\src\AutoDocJson` | `AutoDocJson.Web.dll` | 5280 | `/AutoDocJson` |
| **GrainPriceListWeb** | `C:\opt\src\GrainPriceList` | `GrainPriceListWeb.dll` | 5123 | `/GrainPriceListWeb` |

All apps reference `DedgeAuth.Client` and run as IIS virtual applications under `Default Web Site` on port 80.

## Publish: Single App

From the app's project root:
```powershell
.\Build-And-Publish.ps1
```

## Publish: All Apps at Once

From the DedgeAuth project root:
```powershell
.\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1             # Build DedgeAuth first, then all consumer apps
.\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1 -DryRun     # Show what would be built without building
.\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1 -SkipDedgeAuth # Only rebuild consumer apps
```

## IIS Deploy: Single App

After publishing, deploy to IIS:
```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-DeployApp.ps1" -SiteName <AppName>
```

## IIS Deploy: All Apps

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"
```

## /publish Command (per-app)

When the user requests `/publish`, perform these two steps:
1. `.\Build-And-Publish.ps1` (from the current project root)
2. `IIS-DeployApp.ps1 -SiteName <ThisAppName>`

Do NOT run `Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1` or `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` unless explicitly asked.

## Publish Profiles (.pubxml)

- `WebApp-FileSystem.pubxml` -- ASP.NET Core web apps (IIS-hosted)
- `WinApp-FileSystem.pubxml` -- background services / console apps
- Always set BOTH `PublishUrl` and `PublishDir` to the same UNC staging path
- Do NOT create or suggest Web Deploy (MSDeploy) profiles

## Deploy Templates

Location: `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\templates\`
Naming: `<SiteName>_<InstallSource>.deploy.json`

Deploy steps: Teardown existing -> Install files -> Create app pool -> Create virtual app -> Generate web.config -> Set permissions -> Start -> Health check

## Auto-Deploy After Major Changes

After a **major change** (DedgeAuth.Client, middleware, multiple consumer apps):

1. `.\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1`
2. `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1`
3. Verify all apps via health checks

## Impact Rules

| Change | Action |
|--------|--------|
| DedgeAuth.Client | Rebuild ALL consumer apps (`Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1`) |
| DedgeAuth wwwroot CSS/JS | Rebuild DedgeAuth only; consumers fetch via proxy |
| Tenant branding | Update `tenants` table; no rebuild |
| Deploy templates | Run `IIS-DeployApp\_deploy.ps1` to sync to servers |
| Single consumer app | Rebuild that app, then `IIS-DeployApp.ps1 -SiteName <Name>` |
